                    <head>Guillelmus Peraldus, Sermons for Sundays</head>
                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc form="codex">
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support>
                                    <p>
                                        <locusGrp>
                                            <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/>
                                            <locus from="SL1" to="SL2" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <locus from="306" to="306" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <locus from="RCI" to="RCI" scheme="other"/>
                                        </locusGrp>
                                        <material>Parchment</material>
                                        <dimensions type="leaf">
                                            <height quantity="205" unit="mm"/>
                                            <width quantity="145" unit="mm"/>
                                        </dimensions>
                                    </p>
                                </support>
                                <extent>
                                    <measure type="leftFlyleaves" quantity="2" unit="folios"/>
                                    <measure type="rightFlyleaves" quantity="1" unit="folios"/>
                                </extent>
                                <foliation>Modern foliation in pencil. From <locus from="290r" to="290r" scheme="folios"/> onwards the foliation is corrected in places (e.g. <locus from="290r" to="290r" scheme="folios"/> first foliated as <quote>f. 300</quote>). <locus from="306" to="306" scheme="folios"/> is a flyleaf and not part of the textblock. <secFol>te regendum miche</secFol>
                                </foliation>
                                <collation>
                                    <formula>1-7(12), 8(12, lacks 12), 9-25(12), 26(6)</formula>
                                    <p>
                                        <ref target="https://vceditor.library.upenn.edu/project/6867c614187d5a0001fdb1d4/viewOnly">VisColl collation </ref>
                                    </p>
                                    <signatures>Quire signatures in Roman numerals at the end of each quire. The two texts in the manuscripts have separate quire signatures. <locus from="1" to="95" scheme="folios"/> carry the signatures <quote>I<hi rend="super">us</hi>
                                        </quote> to <quote>VI<hi rend="super">us</hi>
                                        </quote> (signatures on last two quires lost due to trimming and missing leaf); <locus from="96" to="305" scheme="folios"/> carry the signatures <quote>Ius</quote> to <quote>XIIII<hi rend="super">us</hi>
                                        </quote> (q. 18 and q. 19 both carry the signature <quote>X<hi rend="super">us</hi>
                                        </quote>, q. 24 has lost its signature due to trimming, q. 25 lacks signature).</signatures>
                                    <catchwords>Catchwords by the scribe.</catchwords>
                                </collation>
                            </supportDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <additions>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/>
                                <note>Top of page: faded or partially erased notes by several hands; below in ink by a medieval hand: <quote>liber monasterii Sancte marie virignis in watzstenum</quote>; bottom left corner, in ink by a modern hand: <quote>NESCHER 228</quote>.</note>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="L1r" to="L1r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <note>Top of page, in ink by a medieval hand: <quote>E primo 4<hi rend="super">us</hi>
                                    </quote>;</note>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="L1v" to="L1v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <note>Top left corner, in ink by a modern hand: <quote>NESCHER 228</quote>.</note>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="L2v" to="L2v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <note>Top of page, in ink by a medieval hand: a table of contents.</note>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="306v" to="306v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <note> Top of page, in ink by a medieval hand: <quote>probacio?</quote>; below: <quote>liber Monasterii Sancte Marie Virignis in Watzstenum</quote>; below: <quote>-igo?</quote>.</note>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="RCI" to="RCI" scheme="other"/>
                                <note>Top of page, in ink by a modern hand: annotations in Swedish which seem to concern the price of parchment.</note>
                            </p>
                        </additions>
                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="true">
                                <p>Medieval binding. White/light brown leather over wooden boards. 6 double raised bands and endbands. 2 pin clasps with pins on <locus from="RCO" to="RCO" scheme="other"/>. <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>, in ink: <quote>Sermones in ewangelio <unclear quantity="12" unit="chars"/>
                                    </quote>; stamped in gold: <quote>A 188</quote>.</p>
                                <p>
                                    <dimensions type="binding">
                                        <height quantity="215" unit="mm"/>
                                        <width quantity="155" unit="mm"/>
                                        <depth quantity="75" unit="mm"/>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </p>
                                <condition>Leather worn. One clasp missing.</condition>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>
                                <origPlace>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100111">France</placeName>
                                </origPlace>, <origDate notAfter="1350" notBefore="1275">13th century, late, or 14th century early</origDate>. Provenance and dating based on paleographical features.</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>At some point during the late middle ages the manuscript was acquired by <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100098">Vadstena abbey</orgName>(see owner's marks on <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/> and <locus from="306v" to="306v" scheme="folios"/>, and the shelf mark on <locus from="L1r" to="L1r" scheme="folios"/>). After the dissolution of the monastery the manuscript may have ended up on the private market. During the late 18th/early 19th century it belonged to the book collector <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102711">Daniel Georg Nescher</persName>.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>Acquired by the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100004">National Library</orgName> at the estate auction of <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102711">Daniel Georg Nescher</persName> in <date when="1828"/>.</p>
                        </acquisition>
                    </history>
